(795,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',2,'medium',1,1,'Which layer of the OSI model is responsible for web browsing?','The application layer provides services like web browsing.',1),
(796,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',2,'medium',1,1,'Which protocol is used to access web pages securely?','HTTPS ensures secure web communication.',1),
(797,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'What is the purpose of an IP packet?','An IP packet carries data across networks.',1),
(798,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'Which device assigns IP addresses automatically?','A DHCP server assigns IP addresses dynamically.',1),
(799,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'What is the function of a gateway?','A gateway connects different networks together.',1),
(800,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'What is the role of a MAC address?','A MAC address uniquely identifies a device on a local network.',1),
(801,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'Which of the following is a private IP address?','Private IP addresses are used within local networks.',1),
(802,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'What is the purpose of a subnet mask?','A subnet mask defines network and host portions of an IP address.',1),
(803,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'Which protocol resolves IP addresses to MAC addresses?','ARP maps IP addresses to MAC addresses.',1),
(804,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',3,'medium',1,1,'Which protocol resolves MAC addresses to IP addresses?','Reverse ARP (RARP) resolves MAC to IP addresses.',1),
(805,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'Why is DHCP important in large networks?','DHCP automates IP address assignment, reducing manual configuration.',1),
(806,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'What happens when two devices share the same IP address?','IP conflict occurs, causing communication issues.',1),
(807,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'How does NAT improve network security?','NAT hides internal IP addresses from external networks.',1),
(808,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'What is the main advantage of using IPv6 over IPv4?','IPv6 provides more unique IP addresses.',1),
(809,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'Why is DNS caching beneficial?','DNS caching speeds up domain name resolution.',1),
(810,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'What is the purpose of SSL/TLS?','SSL/TLS encrypts data transmitted over networks.',1),
(811,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'How do firewalls enhance network security?','Firewalls monitor and control incoming and outgoing traffic.',1),
(812,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'What is port forwarding used for?','Port forwarding directs external traffic to specific internal devices.',1),
(813,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'Why are protocols layered in networking?','Layering simplifies design and troubleshooting.',1),
(814,1,1,'mcq','S2/SS1','Internet and WWW',4,'hard',1,1,'What is the main function of ICMP?','ICMP is used for error reporting and diagnostics.',1);
